<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-18T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="104" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72Su/33</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Liaison Officer with the Supreme
                                    War Council</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FAH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frazier</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-18T16:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>23. At the close of the conference on the 16th instant the British
                                and Italian Prime Ministers, accompanied by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> and <pb facs="0260" n="168" xml:id="pg_168"/>
                                <persName>Signor Bissolati</persName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d104fn1">Italian diplomatic representative on the Supreme War
                                    Council.</note> adjourned to the Foreign Office where they were
                                met by the Italian Ambassador in London. At this conference article
                                15 of the secret treaty between Great Britain and Italy was
                                discussed, I was informed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FAH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frazier</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>